## M22.1(1/8): resource-producing temporary `*Foo(...).field` is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 39 (M22.1 "fake-surface audit"): a fresh
## resource allocation `*Foo(...)` allocates a strong Rc, but the
## M20e auto-drop guard only attaches to NAMED bindings. Used as
## an anonymous temporary inside a member access, the Rc leaks
## (strong count stays at 1 forever, allocation never freed).
##
## V1 policy: reject leak-shaped resource rvalues at sema time.
## Hidden-temporary lifetime management is deferred (no V1 use
## case justifies the machinery yet); users bind to a name so the
## M20e guard installs cleanly.

struct User
  age: Int

sub main()
  a = (*User(age: 5)).age   # error: anonymous *User temporary leaks
  print(a)
